.TH "LIGHTNING-LEDGER" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-ledger \- TSV-default view of the SQLite ledger
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning ledger
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning ledger — TSV-default view of the SQLite ledger.

Implements FEAT-193 verbs.

Subcommands:
  list [--account <n>] [--since <date>] [--limit <N>]
  sum  [--by account|day|month|year] [--account <n>]
  balance [<account>]
  annotate <payment_hash> <note>
  add <direction> <amount_msat> [--account <n>] [--peer <p>]
                                 [--payment-hash <h>] [--message <m>]
                                 [--note <n>]
                                      — used by pay/invoice/forward
                                        hooks once they're wired
  export csv|jsonl|tsv
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning ledger <subcommand>

   list [--account <n>] [--since <date>] [--limit <N>]
   sum  [--by account|day|month|year] [--account <n>]
   balance [<account>]
   annotate <payment_hash> <note>
   add <direction> <amount_msat> [--account <n>] [--peer <p>]
       [--payment-hash <h>] [--message <m>] [--note <n>]
   export csv|jsonl|tsv
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
